ry</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAs of December 2012, there were 12 JCI Joint Commission International (JCI) Accredited medical centers in Mexico. (<a href="http://www.jointcommissioninternational.org/JCI-Accredited-Organizations/">http://www.jointcommissioninternational.org/JCI-Accredited-Organizations/</a>\r\n\r\nIn addition, Mexico has the third highest number of surgeons affiliated to the International Society of Aesthetic Plastic Surgery (ISAPS) after United States and Brazil.', 'Mexico Remains the Most Popular Medical Tourism Destination for U.S.', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '91-revision-4', '', '', '2012-12-18 05:49:28', '2012-12-18 05:49:28', '', 91, 'http://www.healthcareabroad.com/blog/91-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
