ral Do’s and Don’ts\n</b></b>\n<ul>\n	<li dir="ltr">Do use professional titles with last names (for example, Dr. Baum).</li>\n	<li dir="ltr">Do make eye contact when communicating.</li>\n	<li dir="ltr">Do learn a little Spanish when going to Argentina.</li>\n	<li dir="ltr">Don’t use first names until you are asked to do so.</li>\n	<li dir="ltr">Don’t make unflattering comparisons between North America and South America.</li>\n	<li dir="ltr">Don’t ask personal questions until you’ve established a good relationship.</li>\n</ul>\n<b><b>\n\n</b></b>\n<h6 dir="ltr" style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #888888;">INFORMATION PROVIDED ON THE SITE IS INTENDED AS A GUIDE ONLY AND SHOULD NOT BE CONSTRUED AS A SUBSTITUTE FOR PROFESSIONAL MEDICAL ADVICE. WE MAKE NO REPRESENTATIONS, WARRANTIES OR UNDERTAKINGS AS TO THE ACCURACY OF ANY INFORMATION PROVIDED ON THIS SITE.</span></h6>\n&nbsp;', '', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '431-revision', '', '', '2013-02-11 08:47:00', '2013-02-11 08:47:00', '', 431, 'http://www.healthcareabroad.com/blog/431-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
